—— Kwame Nkrumah, Neocolonialism (1965)
%
The result of neocolonialism is that foreign capital is used for the exploitation rather than for the development of the less developed parts of the world. Investment under neocolonialism increases rather than decreases the gap between the rich and poor countries of the world.

—— Kwame Nkrumah, Neocolonialism (1965)
%
Neocolonialism is the worst form of imperialism. For those who practice it, it means power without responsibility, and for those who suffer from it, it means exploitation without redress.

—— Kwame Nkrumah, Neocolonialism (1965)
%
