—— Kwame Nkrumah, Neocolonialism (1965)
%
Neocolonialism is based upon the principle of breaking up former large united colonial territories into a number of small non-viable States which are incapable of independent development and must rely upon the former imperial power for defense and even internal security. Their economic and financial systems are linked, as in colonial days, with those of the former colonial ruler.

—— Kwame Nkrumah, Neocolonialism (1965)
%
